<title>
Manual Transaxle Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206010">Manual Transaxle Unit Dismounting and Remounting</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206014">Fifth Gear Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206013">Manual Transaxle Assembly Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206018">Input Shaft and Countershaft Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206012">Gear Shift and Select Shaft Assembly Removal and Installation</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B5206015001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove gear shift &#38; select shaft assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B5206012"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove input shaft 5th gear and countershaft 5th gear. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B5206014"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove left case plate bolts (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove left case plate (1) and bearing set shim (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove snap ring (6) using snap ring pliers (4).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A522018.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "63.883mm" ver = "02" gw = "196" gh = "165"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A522019.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "52.542mm" ver = "01" gw = "187" gh = "132"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.266in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.483in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
5.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Input shaft
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
7.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Input shaft left bearing
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove back up light switch. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B5206007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove reverse gear shaft bolt (1) with gasket.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A522021.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.682mm" ver = "01" gw = "189" gh = "115"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove transaxle case bolts (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B520010.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "99.657mm" ver = "01" gw = "203" gh = "266"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove transaxle left case (1) from transaxle right case (2) using special tool.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B007">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09912-34510">
09912–34510
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure page = "2">
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B520011.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "63.506mm" ver = "01" gw = "227" gh = "164"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove reverse gear shift lever bolts (4) and reverse gear shift lever (5).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull out reverse gear shaft (1) with washer (2), then take off reverse idler gear (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull out 5th &#38; reverse gear shift guide shaft (6) together with 5th &#38; reverse gear shift shaft (7).
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
When removing 5th &#38; reverse gear shift shaft (7) and guide shaft (6), push up high speed gear shift shaft and shift it to 4th to facilitate removal of 5th &#38; reverse shift shaft.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B520012.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "70.922mm" ver = "01" gw = "174" gh = "185"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove countershaft left bearing outer race (1) from transaxle left case (2) using special tool.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B008">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-70123">
09913–70123
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A522025.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.951mm" ver = "01" gw = "124" gh = "125"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential side oil seal. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B5206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential side bearing retainer (1) as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Remove retainer bolts and turn retainer counterclockwise until it stops.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Remove retainer prying it with 2 flat-bladed rods (2).
</ptxt>
</s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0A520034.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "48.687mm" ver = "01" gw = "194" gh = "122"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove O-ring from differential side bearing retainer.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential side shim.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential side bearing outer race from left case (1) using special tools.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B009">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09924-74510">
09924–74510
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B010">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09926-27610">
09926–27610
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0A520035.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.259mm" ver = "01" gw = "170" gh = "126"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
By tapping input shaft end with plastic hammer, push it out as assembly from case a little, then remove input shaft assembly (1), countershaft assembly (2), high speed gear shift shaft (3) and low speed gear shift shaft (4) all at once.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520035.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "39.994mm" ver = "01" gw = "135" gh = "96"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential assembly from transaxle right case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B5206015002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Be sure to use new bolt with pre-coated adhesive. Otherwise, bolt may loosen.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install differential assembly into transaxle right case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Join input shaft (5), countershaft (4), low speed gear shift shaft (2) and high speed gear shift shaft (3) assemblies all together, then install them into transaxle right case (1).
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure not to damage oil seal by input shaft spline while installing.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Make sure that countershaft is engaged with final gear.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520080.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "36.522mm" ver = "01" gw = "116" gh = "87"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install 5th &#38; reverse gear shift shaft (1) with 5th &#38; reverse gear shift guide shaft (2) into transaxle right case (5). Reverse gear shift arm (4) has to be joined with reverse gear shift lever (3) at the same time.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B520013.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "67.888mm" ver = "01" gw = "178" gh = "176"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Mate reverse idler gear (1) with reverse gear shift lever (2), insert reverse gear shaft (3) and washer (6) into case (4) through idler gear and then align bolt hole (7) on shaft with notch (8) on case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten reverse gear shift lever bolts (5) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Be sure to use new reverse gear shift lever bolt with pre-coated adhesive. Otherwise, bolt may loosen.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5B013">
<t-part>
Reverse gear shift lever bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A522028.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "101.250mm" ver = "02" gw = "187" gh = "270"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install right case to left case as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Clean mating surfaces of right case and left case.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Apply specified amount of sealant to left case (1) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<materials>
<materialitem name = "SUZUKI Bond No.1217G" id = "M5B007" uid = "-491504098">
<m-part>
“A”
</m-part>
<m-desc>
Sealant
</m-desc>
<m-number>
99000–31260
</m-number>
<m-name>
SUZUKI Bond No.1217G
</m-name>
</materialitem>
</materials>
<spec>
<title>
Sealant amount for left case
</title>
<ptxt>
“a”: 1.5 mm (0.059 in.)
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A520020.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.847mm" ver = "01" gw = "188" gh = "130"/>
</figure>
</spec>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Mate right case with left case.
</ptxt>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten transaxle case bolts to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5B014">
<t-part>
Transaxle case bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B520014.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "99.657mm" ver = "01" gw = "208" gh = "266"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new reverse gear shaft bolt (1) and new gasket, and tighten it to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5B015">
<t-part>
Reverse gear shaft bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A522030.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.942mm" ver = "01" gw = "194" gh = "125"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
To seat differential side bearing outer race to bearing cone, tap differential side bearing outer race using special tool and plastic hammer.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B011">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09926-27610">
09926–27610
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RH01520053.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.229mm" ver = "01" gw = "149" gh = "115"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Select differential side shim as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Measure depth “a” from left case (1) face to differential side bearing outer race (2) using depth gauge.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Measure height “b” of differential side bearing retainer using depth gauge.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Calculate shim thickness by formula below.
</ptxt>
